        "author": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@yahoo.com",
          "date": "2017-08-14 18:25:19.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-08-28 06:25:39.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9019 mdd: migrate from jiffies64 to ktime",
        "message": "LU-9019 mdd: migrate from jiffies64 to ktime\n\nThe mdd layer uses cfs_time_xxx_64() for 64 bit time percision.\nThis was written before ktime_t came into existence and it uses\n64 bit version of jiffies which can vary between nodes due to\nHZ being configurable. This provides a consistent format with\nnanosecond precision on any node.\n\nChange-Id: Ibec17227fd70a148c83296e8d1c41668f67e9201\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/28407\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
